<title>USA: M.A. Hanna Co Q1 oper net income rises.</title>
<headline>M.A. Hanna Co Q1 oper net income rises.</headline>
<dateline>CLEVELAND 1997-04-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>FIRST QUARTER				   1997	   1996</p>
<p> Net Sales					$527,629     $497,451</p>
<p> Income Before Extraordinary Charge	 15,228	 13,353</p>
<p>     Extraordinary charge			    -	(1,575)</p>
<p> Net Income					 15,228	 11,778</p>
<p> Net EPS Primary Before charge		   .34	    .29</p>
<p>  Extraordinary charge				 -	   (.03)</p>
<p>  Net primary EPS				    .34	    .26</p>
<p> Net fully diluted EPS before charge	   .33	    .28</p>
<p>	     Extraordinary charge		    -	  (.03)</p>
<p>	     Net income				.33	    .25</p>
<p>Average number of common shares</p>
<p>	 Primary				44,996,787   45,723,759</p>
<p>	 Fully diluted			46,014,396   47,014,867</p>
<p>	     (All Data Above 000s Except Per Share Numbers)</p>
<p>NOTE: 1996 EPS data restated to reflect a 3-for-2 stock split effective May 24, 1996.</p>
<p>Currency exchange had a 1 percentage point negative impact on sales.</p>
<p>During the first quarter of 1996, M.A. Hanna purchased $34.5 million of its 9 percent notes due in 1998 at an after-tax premium of $1.6 million, or 3 cents per share, fully diluted, which was taken as an extraordinary charge.</p>
<p>Debt-to-capital was 32.0 percent at the end of the first three months of 1997.  During the first quarter of 1997, the company repurchased 373,000 shares of stock.</p>
